headline: These 2 Retailers Were a Bright Spot During Earnings Season. What They Have In Common.
summary: In its most recent quarter, as Barron’s Sabrina Escobar noted, Walmart reported adjusted earnings of 58 cents a share for the period ended in October, while the consensus forecast on Wall Street was for 53 cents.  Walmart’s revenue increased 5.5% to $169.6 billion, while analysts polled by FactSet were expecting $167.7 billion.  Since reporting on Nov. 18, Walmart’s stock is up nearly 12%.

headline: Costco price target raised to $907 from $755 at Roth MKM
summary: Roth MKM raised the firm’s price target on Costco (COST) to $907 from $755 and keeps a Neutral rating on the shares after its Q1 earnings beat. The company is capturing a channel shift toward at-home consumption, though its renewal rates decreased by 10bps, with digital renewals weighing on growth, the analyst tells investors in a research note. headline: Costco price target raised to $1,030 from $1,020 at Evercore ISI
